Review:
I've been looking for my whole life without money. 
1. Opened a cafe; 
2. Hired workers;
3. Ordered a lot of goods;
4. Without profit, got into debt;
5. Became bankrupt;
6. My wife kicked me out of the house.

Pros:
1)AI is gathering fleets in one big plob during the war now;
2)AI became better at building economy;
3)Game became faster (both in performance sense and in game(no more restrictions for science labs and rare resources production buildings));
4)New Megastructures and switch of payment for spy operation from energy to influence allows you at least some way to spend it.
Cons:
1)AI fleet composition is awfull (mix of all ship types in the end-game (after 2285) ); it results in AI fleets being desintegrated by 2 times smaller fleets;
2)It looks like AI doesn't consider overlord power, when declares war on vassal (same issue with guarantee independence);
3)vassals are broken: basically the only two ways to make them pay you anything are either to subjigate them by tributary war, second - send them new terms of vassalization over and over again untill they wouldn't have enough influence to refuse (didn't try myself);
4)Heard that low stability dilemmas are impossible to resolve without revolts; didn't experience this issue myself, but AI is definately struggling with it.
Overall, AI became better, new buildings look cool, game performing better and gameplay was speed up as well.
Hower, I would recommend you not to buy this DLC before Paradox releases patch,which will fix the issues I mentioned in points 3 and 4. Since Steam doesn't have "Debatable" as mark - I will pick "Thumb up" option.
